summary: CONSUMER NOTICED THAT THE AIR PRESSURE IN THE TIRES WAS ALWAYS LOW, CONSUMER THOUGHT IT TO BE THE TIRES AND REPLACED THEM, IN REPLACING THE TIRES THE CONSUMER FOUND THE VEHICLE HAD COME WITH THE WRONG SIZE TIRES, THE PROBLEM WITH THE PRESSURE STILL OCCURRED UNTIL A DEALER EXAMINED THE PROBLEM MORE THOROUGHLY AND FOUND THE RIMS TO BE THE CAUSE DUE TO 2 OF THE RIMS NOT BEING SEALED PROPERLY.
